{"found_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/", "full_description": "COMPANY\n\nAccuWeather, recognized and documented as the most accurate source of weather forecasts and warnings in the world, has saved tens of thousands of lives, prevented hundreds of thousands of injuries and tens of billions of dollars in property damage. With global headquarters in State College, PA and other offices around the world, AccuWeather serves more than 1.5 billion people daily to help them plan their lives and get more out of their day through innovative digital media properties, such as AccuWeather.com and mobile, as well as Business solutions (AES), radio, television, newspapers, and the 24/7 AccuWeather Network.\n\nAdditionally, AccuWeather produces and distributes news, weather content, and video for more than 180,000 third-party websites. Among AccuWeather\u2019s many innovative and award-winning features free to the public are MinuteCast\u00ae Minute by Minute\u2122 forecasts with Superior Accuracy\u2122.\u00a0 Further, AccuWeather serves more than half of Fortune 500 companies and thousands of businesses globally.\n\n\n\nSUMMARY\n\nAccuWeather is seeking an experienced\nSenior Agency Sales Director\nto help build and sell advertising solutions to our key partners benefiting from our proven conversion driven and brand building solutions. You\u2019ll contribute to a high-caliber team in a business that is experiencing rapid and dramatic growth. We are looking for demonstrated performance in a constantly changing, ambiguous environment; and problem-solving leadership with limited oversight.\n\nThis role will manage Agency relationships with a\nfocus on the C-Suite, Agency Investment Leads, Brand Teams, Buying Teams, Programmatic Buying Arms and Data Analytics & Strategy Teams.\nIn partnership with upper management, this role will develop a strategy specific to assigned holding companies, while driving AccuWeather\u2019s data, measurement, media, and analytics revenue. This position requires extensive knowledge of the changing agency & media landscape, the drive to develop industry-transforming strategies and the ability to build relationships with senior agency management. The ideal candidate has media agency planning experience, a deep knowledge of measurement & analytics used to evaluate performance, and a proven ability to influence multiple levels of an organization.\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES\n\n\n\nBuild AccuWeather\u2019s annual and quarterly Strategic Plan for assigned agencies, including analysis of Agency revenue\n\nOversee bottom-up quota setting across markets and ensure functional \u2018voice of the agency\u2019 input is comprehended prior to final AOP\n\nBuild and elevate relationships at the highest levels within the assigned agencies, C-Suite, Senior Agency Influencers to continuously uncover strategic opportunities to drive AccuWeather revenue on a global, regional, and local level\n\nIdentify and lead the development of joint business projects and/or beta opportunities with assigned agencies.\n\nServe as internal voice of the agency customer to help shape product and marketing roadmaps\n\nAgency account management including, but not limited to: maintaining contact lists, establishing meeting cadence with (internal and external) key stakeholders, seeking out new relationships/contacts, developing quarterly business reviews, organizing and coordinating agency education initiatives (cross discipline agency days and/or training sessions), fulfilling ad hoc agency request and breaking down obstacle.\n\nContribute to AccuWeather\u2019s tentpole senior-level engagements and activations (i.e. CES, Cannes) with assigned agencies\n\nPartner with Global Accounts and National sales teams to contribute to and uncover category and client-level opportunities globally and regionally at both the Agency and Brand level\n\nCollaborate with a number of internal specialists (i.e. data, platform, measurement, media, analytics) as needed to meet revenue requirements and to continuously identify relevant opportunities for your agencies\n\nDevelop and negotiate trading agreements at an agency holding company level\n\nBe a trusted thought leader to both external stakeholders and investment teams by leading consistent agency education initiatives and events, act as an ambassador and spokesperson for AccuWeather in the agency community\n\nOperate at the \u2018tip of the spear\u2019, immersing in industry shifts (in-housing, rise of independent agencies and consultancies etc) and competitive offerings, to bring an \u2018outside-in\u2019 perspective, framing new sales initiatives and recommendations\n\nDevelop network of strong relationships with key search and media industry influencers, customers and partners\n\nIdentify, grow and retain the best and brightest talent, while fostering an open, diverse and inclusive culture.\n\n\n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\n\n\n\nBA/BS degree required\n\n5+ years digital ad sales experience a focus on media, lower-funnel conversion strategies, data and analytics\n\nDemonstrated ability to think strategically about a particular industry and/or product set.\n\nComfortable with presenting to clients and agencies\u2014in both small or large groups\n\nFamiliarity with agency holding companies and strong relationships across the agency landscape\n\nAbility to partner within cross-functional teams\n\nAbility to consult and bring ideas to the table\n\nStrong teamwork and collaboration skills\n\nAbility to build internal networks to accomplish goals through collaboration with resources across teams\n\nStrong writing and copy-editing skills\n\nA self-starter who takes initiative and is action oriented\n\nCan balance the need for quick turnaround with longer-term strategic efforts\n\nIs flexible and can deal effectively with changes in priorities or ambiguity\n\nIs driven and solution-oriented and can overcome obstacles to drive projects through completion\n\nComfortable with a fast-paced, always-on, start-up environment\n\n\n\n\nPREFERRED\nQUALIFICATIONS\n\n\n\nDemonstrated Marketing Automation and Programmatic Advertising expertise\n\nExhibits a high level of competency in oral and written communication skills\n\nDemonstrated expertise in building relationships with senior agency decision makers\n\n\n\n\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer. We provide equal opportunity to all qualified individuals regardless of race, color, religion, age, genetic information, gender, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, national origin, veteran orientation, or veteran status, pregnancy, disability, marital status or any other legally protected categories under local, state of federal laws.\u00a0 We believe a culture of diversity and inclusion provides unique perspectives that help make the workplace more innovative, engaging and profitable.", "job_location": "New York, NY", "job_title": "Senior Agency Sales Director", "job_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/jobs/1926357", "seen_time_epoch": 1577549228, "short_description": null, "tags_string": null}
{"found_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/", "full_description": "COMPANY\n\nAccuWeather, recognized and documented as the most accurate source of weather forecasts and warnings in the world, has saved tens of thousands of lives, prevented hundreds of thousands of injuries and tens of billions of dollars in property damage. With global headquarters in State College, PA and other offices around the world, AccuWeather serves more than 1.5 billion people daily to help them plan their lives and get more out of their day through innovative digital media properties, such as AccuWeather.com and mobile, as well as Business solutions (AES), radio, television, newspapers, and the 24/7 AccuWeather Network.\n\nAdditionally, AccuWeather produces and distributes news, weather content, and video for more than 180,000 third-party websites. Among AccuWeather\u2019s many innovative and award-winning features free to the public are MinuteCast\u00ae Minute by Minute\u2122 forecasts with Superior Accuracy\u2122.\u00a0 Further, AccuWeather serves more than half of Fortune 500 companies and thousands of businesses globally.\n\n\n\nSUMMARY\n\nReporting directly to the Controller, the Compliance Coordinator is responsible for coordinating all tax and compliance for AccuWeather\u2019s domestic and 6 international locations in partnership with our external accounting firm.\n\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES:\n\n\nAssist external accountants with our US and international tax return preparation\n\nResearch and provide recommendations on tax compliance issues, both foreign and domestic\n\nAssist in managing the international tax advisors provided by our external accountants\n\nPrepare a schedule and calendar memorializing our Federal, State, and international tax filing requirements, as well as other statutory compliance requirements\n\nReview and manage our R&D tax credit process\n\nReview IRS and State tax communications with outside firm\n\nReview and manage our sales and use tax compliance requirements\n\nAssist with IRS or State tax audits\n\n\n\n\nBACKGROUND AND QUALIFICATIONS\n\n\nBachelor\u2019s degree in Accounting or related field or a combination of education and experience is required\n\nCPA or MBA preferred\n\n2-4 years of public accounting, audit or tax experience\n\nKnowledge of accounting systems is preferred\n\nKnowledge of Management Reporter or other equivalent financial reporting program is preferred\n\nExperience with SharePoint or other shared file services is preferred\n\nHave an ability to manage and analyze departmental financial reports\n\nKnowledge of Microsoft Excel and Word are required\n\nMust be a self-starter who is extremely organized and detail oriented\n\nShould have strong customer service skills (customers being employees)\n\nExcellent communication skills, both verbal and written\n\nRegular and predictable attendance is an essential for this position\n\n\n\n\n\n\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer. We provide equal opportunity to all qualified individuals regardless of race, color, religion, age, genetic information, gender, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, national origin, veteran orientation, or veteran status, pregnancy, disability, marital status or any other legally protected categories under local, state of federal laws.\u00a0 We believe a culture of diversity and inclusion provides unique perspectives that help make the workplace more innovative, engaging and profitable.", "job_location": "State College, PA", "job_title": "Finance Compliance Coordinator", "job_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/jobs/1900582", "seen_time_epoch": 1577549228, "short_description": null, "tags_string": null}
{"found_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/", "full_description": "COMPANY\n\nAccuWeather, recognized and documented as the most accurate source of weather forecasts and warnings in the world, not only has saved tens of thousands of lives, prevented hundreds of thousands of injuries and tens of billions of dollars in property damage, but also has woven in and out of peoples lives through the experience of weather. Through our innovative digital media properties, such as AccuWeather.com and mobile, Business solutions (AES), radio, television, newspapers, and the 24/7 AccuWeather Network,\u00a0 we reach more than 1.5 billion people every day with information that is an integral part of their daily decisions, from the biggest to the smallest ones.\n\nAccuWeather serves more than half of Fortune 500 companies and thousands of businesses globally, and produces and distributes news, weather content, and video for more than 180,000 third-party websites. Among AccuWeather\u2019s many innovative and award-winning features free to the public are MinuteCast\u00ae Minute by Minute\u2122 forecasts with Superior Accuracy\u2122.\u00a0 Headquartered in State College, PA, AccuWeather is a global company with (FILL IN) offices around the world.\n\n\n\nSUMMARY\n\nReporting directly to the Founder/CEO, the Chief Marketing Officer (with a dotted-line reporting to the Chief Business officer) will be responsible for developing a cohesive strategic marketing vision and execution plan to drive stronger brand awareness, voice, reach, relevance, impact, influence, conversion and analytics, to achieve AccuWeather\u2019s objectives of growth, profitability and visibility globally. The CMO will be responsible for overseeing \u2013 and planning, organizing, staffing and executing all functions related to -- marketing, advertising and promotional campaigns, websites, branding strategies, marketing of new products and services, public relations, social media and CRM programs by working with the executive team. The CMO will play an important collaborative role in providing product support and leading product launches, and in addition, will have responsibility for developing consistent messaging and training to increase the effectiveness of sales efforts, partnerships and channels. The CMO will have ultimate responsibility for the performance and management of the outside PR firm, and also coordinate closely with other communications functions within the firm.\n\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES\n\n\nPartner with Business Development team to build proactive growth platforms based on qualitative and quantitative user insights/data, segmentation and journeys\n\nDevelop cohesive marketing point of view for US and international execution across Go-To-Market, Sales and Marketing channels to deliver on brand promise across AccuWeather\u2019s portfolio, including:\n\nDigital Media Advertising and Partnership Acquisition\n\nEnterprise Solutions\n\nTV, Radio, Newspaper Businesses\n\nThe AccuWeather Network\n\nData Driven Decisions\n\n\n\nLeverage marketing mix holistically to drive customer acquisition & retention while improving overall efficiency and consistency across:\n\nAdvertising\n\nOwned and Earned Digital Demand Generation\n\nPR & Corporate Communications\n\nPromotional Programs\n\nSales Collateral and RFPs\n\n\n\nPartner with cross-functional leaders across sales, business development, product development and IT to drive successful new product launches\n\nImprove marketing programs to support AccuWeather\u2019s critical partnerships to increase brand reach\n\nImprove presence and influence of Executives and Board Members to help support brand and reputational objectives through content marketing and thought leadership strategies on appropriate social channels\n\nIdentification of trends and innovation\n\nManage vendors and agencies and coordination with internal staff functions\n\nDevelop and prioritize plans for international expansion and growth\n\n\n\n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\n\n\nA Bachelor\u2019s degree in Marketing or similar field or equivalent combination of education and experience is required. An MBA in Marketing is preferred.\n\nDemonstrated experience growing a brand and helping maximize company revenue\n\nStrong creative insight and ability to inspire others to share his/her creative vision.\n\nProven ability work with and influence executives at the highest levels\n\nDeep understanding of and substantial experience with Digital Media required\n\nAbility to assess talent and build high performing teams a must\n\nPrevious experience leading a successful and creative marketing team\n\nDemonstrated ability to put strategic vision into motion\n\nExperience with analytics and measurement methods, and the ability to use market research and analysis to drive and support strategic decision making\n\nProven ability to develop advertising and promotional programs and campaigns\n\nMust have strong communications skills both oral and written\n\nMust have experience in the PR and communication space - managing outside Agencies of Record\n\n\n\n\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer. We provide equal opportunity to all qualified individuals regardless of race, color, religion, age, genetic information, gender, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, national origin, veteran orientation, or veteran status, pregnancy, disability, marital status or any other legally protected categories under local, state of federal laws.\u00a0 We believe a culture of diversity and inclusion provides unique perspectives that help make the workplace more innovative, engaging and profitable.", "job_location": "New York, NY", "job_title": "Chief Marketing Officer", "job_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/jobs/1971188", "seen_time_epoch": 1577549228, "short_description": null, "tags_string": null}
{"found_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/", "full_description": "C\nOMPANY\n\n\nAccuWeather, recognized and documented as the most accurate source of weather forecasts and warnings in the world, has saved tens of thousands of lives, prevented hundreds of thousands of injuries and tens of billions of dollars in property damage. With global headquarters in State College, PA and other offices around the world, AccuWeather serves more than 1.5 billion people daily to help them plan their lives and get more out of their day through innovative digital media properties, such as AccuWeather.com and mobile, as well as Business Solutions (AES), radio, television, newspapers, and the 24/7 AccuWeather Network.\n\nAdditionally, AccuWeather produces and distributes news, weather content, and video for more than 180,000 third-party websites. Among AccuWeather\u2019s many innovative and award-winning features free to the public are MinuteCast\u00ae Minute by Minute\u2122 forecasts with Superior Accuracy\u2122.\u00a0 Further, AccuWeather serves more than half of Fortune 500 companies and thousands of businesses globally.\n\nSUMMARY\n\nThe Senior Director of Information Security is responsible for leading the strategy, administration, and operations of our information security program. This role will engage broadly across business and information technology functions to ensure effective awareness, planning, and execution on security-related concepts, projects, initiatives, and requirements. The successful candidate will have a diverse technical background, professional security credentials, demonstrated effectiveness in management and leadership, effective business acumen, excellent written and verbal communication skills, and exceptional interpersonal skills.\n\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES:\n\n\nProactively lead and manage information security, information assurance, and cyber defense for the company.\n\nDefine the vision, strategy, tactics and a roadmap for security practices and solutions that follow industry- and vendor-recommended best practices.\n\nEstablish and maintain an Information Security Management System (ISMS) in compliance with ISO/IEC 27001 and related standards.\n\nDevelop, implement, and/or maintain procedures and automated processes to monitor and respond to security events involving computers, networks, accounts, and services.\n\nDevelop, implement, and/or maintain procedures and automated processes to ensure the security of internally-developed software and/or technology products.\n\nRoutinely test and assess the organization\u2019s security measures, identifying and remediating any weak points that may be vulnerable to attack and constitute an unacceptable risk.\n\nDevelop strategies, processes, and procedures to address security incidents.\n\nDrive fulfillment of the technological and business requirements for Service Organization Control (SOC) reports based on SSAE 18.\n\nPrepare regular technical and executive reports on security status, initiatives, and overall landscape.\n\nPartner closely with technology, legal, and business representatives to help ensure compliance with GDPR, CCPA, and other privacy requirements.\n\nCoordinate the development and implementation of Identity Management principles and standards including regular periodic reviews of each.\n\nReview, refresh, and develop security policies as required.\n\n\n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\n:\n\n\nA Bachelor\u2019s degree in Information Systems, Cybersecurity, or a related field or an equivalent combination of education and experience. An advanced degree is preferred.\n\n7+ years of personnel management in a technology environment.\n\n10+ years of technical management/administration of technology and/or information systems.\n\nCISSP, CISM, CISA, GIAM or a similar security certification is required.\n\nCIPP certification is desirable.\n\nDirect experience with one or more cloud platforms is required. Azure is strongly preferred.\n\nStrong knowledge of Identity and Access Management (IAM), Single Sign-On (SSO), Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA), and general access controls.\n\nDirect experience with vulnerability management including scanning, penetration testing, and remediation.\n\nDemonstrated understanding of firewalls, access control lists, general routing and switching.\n\nKnowledge of network, system, service, and security monitoring tools, methods, and best practices.\n\nDemonstrated ability to handle and maintain the integrity and confidentiality of highly sensitive material and information.\n\n\n\nFormal management/leadership training is strongly preferred.\n\nOne or more technical certifications, particularly in cloud computing, are preferred.\n\n\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer. We provide equal opportunity to all qualified individuals regardless of race, color, religion, age, genetic information, gender, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, national origin, veteran orientation, or veteran status, pregnancy, disability, marital status or any other legally protected categories under local, state of federal laws.\u00a0 We believe a culture of diversity and inclusion provides unique perspectives that help make the workplace more innovative, engaging and profitable.", "job_location": "State College, PA", "job_title": "Senior Director, Information Security", "job_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/jobs/2010170", "seen_time_epoch": 1577549228, "short_description": null, "tags_string": null}
