eer development.\n\nThis position is based at our Headquarters in State College, Pennsylvania.\n\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES:\n\n\nServe as a key leader within AccuWeather Labs, including engagement and coordination of internal/external innovation \u2018sprints\u2019, and management of the budget and resources.\n\nOperate as subject matter expert in applied meteorology supporting the exploration and realization of solutions that drive AccuWeather\u2019s next generation technologies.\n\nPartner with AccuWeather\u2019s product organization through reviewing, supporting, and driving new potential product and innovation initiatives.\n\nEstablish and manage scientific goals through implementation and improvement of a process of rapid prototyping and development in a cloud-based environment.\n\nWork with cross functional internal teams to bring ideas to life.\n\nMaintain and ensure the use of meteorological technology best practices.\n\n\n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS:\n\n\nM.S. or higher in Atmospheric Science, Computer Science, or a similar, relevant field.\n\nExperience working with data and systems in the cloud.\n\nExperience applying meteorological algorithms, models, or similar technologies to support unique, weather-impacted applications.\n\nCompetency generating high quality code for applications of scientific based solutions.\n\nDesire and experience working in short duration development cycles.\n\nInnovative mindset with a desire to work on a variety of projects.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer. We provide equal opportunity to all qualified individuals regardless of race, color, religion, age, genetic information, gender, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, national origin, veteran orientation, or veteran status, pregnancy, disability, marital status or any other legally protected categories under local, state of federal laws.\u00a0 We believe a culture of diversity and inclusion provides unique perspectives that help make the workplace more innovative, engaging and profitable.", "job_location": "State College, PA", "job_title": "Applied Meteorology & Innovation Lead", "job_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/jobs/2010417", "seen_time_epoch": 1577549228, "short_description": null, "tags_string": null}
{"found_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/", "full_description": "COMPANY\n\nAccuWeather, recognized and documented as the most accurate source of weather forecasts and warnings in the world, has saved tens of thousands of lives, prevented hundreds of thousands of injuries and tens of billions of dollars in property damage. With global headquarters in State College, PA and other offices around the world, AccuWeather serves more than 1.5 billion people daily to help them plan their lives and get more out of their day through innovative digital media properties, such as AccuWeather.com and mobile, as well as Business solutions (AES), radio, television, newspapers, and the 24/7 AccuWeather Network.\n\nAdditionally, AccuWeather produces and distributes news, weather content, and video for more than 180,000 third-party websites. Among AccuWeather\u2019s many innovative and award-winning features free to the public are MinuteCast\u00ae Minute by Minute\u2122 forecasts with Superior Accuracy\u2122.\u00a0 Further, AccuWeather serves more than half of Fortune 500 companies and thousands of businesses globally.\n\nSUMMARY\n\nProduct Manager \u2013 Health and Wellness Initiatives\n\nAccuWeather has ambitious plans to launch a series of health products that serve our global audience. Weather and wellbeing go hand-in-hand and we\u2019re seeking a Product Manager with experience researching, concepting, launching and monetizing digital products that are focused on health and wellness.\n\nThe successful candidate will be joining at a time of enormous potential to quickly execute on a series of ideas, as well as make a mark by using their experience to drive a full product roadmap across AccuWeather\u2019s flagship website and app portfolio; considering both free and subscription offerings.\n\nThis is a leadership position that will have influence across the entire organization, therefore it\u2019s essential to have executive presence and strong business acumen. Given AccuWeather\u2019s enormous audience reach of over 350M monthly actives and a 24/7 editorial operation including cable television network; the Product Manager will take a 360-view of their portfolio to ensure health products are launched, adopted, monetized and integrated within editorial franchises.\n\nIf you\u2019re a driven Product Manager with a passion for the sciences and seeking a global canvass to ship utility products that improve people\u2019s lives, this role is perfectly suited for you. This position reports into the Director of Product within a team comprising of product management, visual design, front-end development and data & analytics; the full product family.\n\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITES\n\n\nDefine the product vision, strategy, and roadmap for the health and wellness portfolio\n\nCollaborate with key stakeholders across the organization to refine health opportunities and publish product launch cadence\n\nLead collaboration across the product organization to ensure products and features are prioritized within web and app roadmaps\n\nDevelop product requirement documents, collaborate with engineering to define requirements\n\nCollaborate with editorial on health and wellness content that support the product roadmap\n\nApproach product discovery with empathetic mindset, applying a toolkit of data-driven & research methodologies\n\nCollaborate with revenue team, including ad sales, to ensure roadmap is monetized and demonstrates ROI; work with business development on new opportunities\n\nPerform market and competitive research within category\n\nInterrogate performance data for insights and leverage appropriately\n\nCrush bugs and rigorously prioritize work\n\nBe the evangelist, and expert, for health and wellness products at AccuWeather\n\n\n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\n\n\nBachelor\u2019s degree in Business, Engineering, Computer Science or Health related\u00a0 (Preferred)\n\n3-5 years of experience in product management with health and wellness expertise\n\nShare tangible examples of previous product launches within health category\n\nProven track record managing product roadmaps in a fast-driven environment\n\nDeep understanding of health and wellness product ecosystems including ads\n\nProven ability to effectively communicate to key stakeholders; be collaborative by nature\n\nComfortable collaborating and leading agile teams including engineers\n\nExceptional organizational and communication skills\n\nStrong presentation skill capabilities\n\n\n\n\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer. We provide equal opportunity to all qualified individuals regardless of race, color, religion, age, genetic information, gender, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, national origin, veteran orientation, or veteran status, pregnancy, disability, marital status or any other legally protected categories under local, state of federal laws.\u00a0 We believe a culture of diversity and inclusion provides unique perspectives that help make the workplace more innovative, engaging and profitable.", "job_location": "New York, NY", "job_title": "Product Manager, Health & Wellness Initiatives", "job_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/jobs/1822422", "seen_time_epoch": 1577549228, "short_description": null, "tags_string": null}
{"found_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/", "full_description": "COMPANY\n\nAccuWeather, recognized and documented as the most accurate source of weather forecasts and warnings in the world, has saved tens of thousands of lives, prevented hundreds of thousands of injuries and tens of billions of dollars in property damage. With global headquarters in State College, PA and other offices around the world, AccuWeather serves more than 1.5 billion people daily to help them plan their lives and get more out of their day through innovative digital media properties, such as AccuWeather.com and mobile, as well as Business solutions (AES), radio, television, newspapers, and the 24/7 AccuWeather Network.\n\nAdditionally, AccuWeather produces and distributes news, weather content, and video for more than 180,000 third-party websites. Among AccuWeather\u2019s many innovative and award-winning features free to the public are MinuteCast\u00ae Minute by Minute\u2122 forecasts with Superior Accuracy\u2122.\u00a0 Further, AccuWeather serves more than half of Fortune 500 companies and thousands of businesses globally.\n\n\n\nSUMMARY\n\nThe AccuWeather Technology organization is seeking an experienced leader that will manage a team of talented software engineers who deliver and maintain the AccuWeather Web and Mobile Web properties.\u00a0 Someone who, in addition to strong management skills, acts as a leader for the technical roadmap, communicates timeline, quality, and financial risks to stakeholders, and collaborates closely with Product and Project leads as well as peers across the organization.\n\nIn addition to strong management skills, you identify areas of strategic technical debt and opportunities for improvement, align the cost/benefit analysis, and clearly communicate the risks, impacts, and recommended timelines. You guide teams, with principles founded on cloud, caching and automation, towards best practices that allow progress to be made efficiently and sustainably.\n\nYou are an independent Senior Manager who is comfortable managing team members with different skill sets from your own. You demonstrate leadership by supporting the growth and development of your team as a whole and individually. You will coach and develop your team to maximize strengths and develop strong, collaborative, partnerships across AccuWeather. Goal setting is integral, and you facilitate your team\u2019s participation in defining priorities and what is important.\n\nThis position is available at our offices in State College, Pennsylvania, and New York City.\n\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES\n\n\nHire, develop, and guide staff responsible for the design, development, and delivery of AccuWeather\u2019s Web and Mobile Web properties\n\nTechnically proficient in the software development life cycle and viewed as a subject matter expert\n\nPossess a deep understanding and experience developing with web technologies including JavaScript, HTML5, CSS, .NET MVC, and .NET Core\n\nEnsures design and delivery of software that is of high quality, HA, monitorable, and maintainable\n\nChampions cloud technologies, automation, continuous improvement, and agile methodologies\n\nReports to business partners and leadership on activities, risks, and issues on key projects\n\nFacilitates team communications and leads discussions across the team and functional groups\n\nRegular management of objectives, priorities, time, risks, mitigations, and performance management of all reporting staff\n\nAssigns areas of ownership; ensures resources have clear priorities and adequate resources\n\nWorks closely with Product Managers on roadmap and sprint planning activities\n\nCommunicates status, risks to schedules, and offers mitigation strategies to ensure on-time delivery of all committed projects across the delivery life cycle\n\nDefines, manages, and reports regularly on Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) that measure team performance against organizational objectives\n\nProvides critical status reporting and updates to Senior Director, Technology on all aspects of web engineering\n\nCoaches team members to progress career goals and personal development goals\n\nContributes to the development of an operating plan and budget\n\nResponsible for coordinating team expenses within a budget or part of a larger budget\n\nCollaborates with external vendors in defining and developing initiatives that support AccuWeather\u2019s business and technology needs\n\nMinimal travel (10%) is required.\n\n\n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\n\n\nBS/BA in related discipline with 10+ years\u2019 experience in related field - OR - MS/MA and 7+ years\u2019 experience in related field\n\nDeep familiarity with global, large scale, responsive, web platforms\n\nExperience managing teams in an Agile software delivery environment\n\nExperience leading or managing major projects or programs within department or functional area with significant business impact\n\nAbility to make prompt, sound decisions when faced with complex and often contradictory alternatives that result in successful outcomes\n\nSelf-driven; strong problem-solving skills; adaptable, proactive, and willing to take ownership\n\nStrong verbal / written communication skills; excellent collaboration, reporting, and analytical skills\n\nRecognized SME in software development, design, and producing deliverables\n\nExperience developing software using industry standard tools and services\n\nWillingness and ability to create and adapt to new technologies\n\n\n\n\n\n\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer. We provide equal opportunity to all qualified individuals regardless of race, color, religion, age, genetic information, gender, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, national origin, veteran orientation, or veteran status, pregnancy, disability, marital status or any other legally protected categories under local, state of federal laws.\u00a0 We believe a culture of diversity and inclusion provides unique perspectives that help make the workplace more innovative, engaging and profitable.", "job_location": "State College, PA or New York, NY", "job_title": "Senior Manager, Web", "job_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/jobs/2008638", "seen_time_epoch": 1577549228, "short_description": null, "tags_string": null}
