rends to help drive tactical and strategic business decisions.\n\n\nTo succeed in this role, you should have strong technical acumen, exceptional problem-solving capabilities and be extremely detail oriented. \u00a0This role is perfectly suited for someone with a passion for data, digital technologies and those interested in leveraging data and technology to improve the end users experience.\n\nYour day-to-day\n\n\nWork with internal or external data partners to collect, organize, and connect various data sources, ranging from ad server data audience analytics data, performance marketing data, third-party revenue, off-platform revenue, etc.\n\nPerform deep dive analysis into specific KPIs to understand the underlying influences\n\nInterface regularly with partners and data team; proactively identify and resolve issues that arise including reporting discrepancies, data inaccuracies\n\nEvaluate existing and develop new metrics, reports, and dashboards\n\nEstablish and maintain a process to govern and educate business teams around A/B testing and personalization\n\nMaintain detailed documentation of analytics tools and measurement strategies\n\nLeverage data visualization tools to curate reporting for cross-functional teams\n\nCollaborate with product management teams and other key stakeholders to define and implement necessary requirements in order to properly report on relevant Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)\n\nProvide digital asset tagging instructions for website and mobile app development teams\n\n\nAbout you\n\n\nMeticulously detailed. Data and Technology savvy\n\nPassion for learning new tools and visualizing data outputs\n\nA genuine interest and knowledge of the media and digital industry landscape\n\nBe curious and globally oriented with pride for building successful products\n\n\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES\n\n\nBachelor\u2019s Degree in computer science, Information Systems, Technical Marketing or equivalent experience/training\n\n3+ years of experience using Google Analytics, or other industry-leading analytics tools and familiarity with web data, traffic from a site tagging and data collection perspective\n\nProficiency in SQL SQL / R / Python / BigQuery a plus\n\nFamiliarity with testing/personalization platforms (ie. Adobe Test & Target, Optimizely, Dynamic Yield)\n\nWorking knowledge of Data visualization dashboards (Looker, Domo, QlikView/QlikSense, Tableau, or any other BI tools)\n\nExperience with data integration or ETL processing related projects\n\nHigh level of attention to detail, quality, and effective oral and written communication skills, along with excellent follow-through\n\nUnderstanding of digital/media/marketing data sources and metrics preferred: Digital (e.g. Web, Social, Display, Search etc.)\n\nWillingness to learn and adapt to a changing environment\n\nExperience in working with, managing and mentoring teams preferred\n\nA genuine interest and knowledge of the media and digital industry landscape\n\n\n\n\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer. We provide equal opportunity to all qualified individuals regardless of race, color, religion, age, genetic information, gender, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, national origin, veteran orientation, or veteran status, pregnancy, disability, marital status or any other legally protected categories under local, state of federal laws.\u00a0 We believe a culture of diversity and inclusion provides unique perspectives that help make the workplace more innovative, engaging and profitable.", "job_location": "New York, NY", "job_title": "Senior Analyst, Digital Analytics", "job_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/jobs/1731910", "seen_time_epoch": 1577549228, "short_description": null, "tags_string": null}
{"found_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/", "full_description": "COMPANY\n\nAccuWeather, recognized and documented as the most accurate source of weather forecasts and warnings in the world, has saved tens of thousands of lives, prevented hundreds of thousands of injuries and tens of billions of dollars in property damage. With global headquarters in State College, PA and other offices around the world, AccuWeather serves more than 1.5 billion people daily to help them plan their lives and get more out of their day through innovative digital media properties, such as AccuWeather.com and mobile, as well as Business solutions (AES), radio, television, newspapers, and the 24/7 AccuWeather Network.\n\nAdditionally, AccuWeather produces and distributes news, weather content, and video for more than 180,000 third-party websites. Among AccuWeather\u2019s many innovative and award-winning features free to the public are MinuteCast\u00ae Minute by Minute\u2122 forecasts with Superior Accuracy\u2122.\u00a0 Further, AccuWeather serves more than half of Fortune 500 companies and thousands of businesses globally.\n\n\n\nSUMMARY\nWant to be part of a team that is a global leader in API traffic, serving nearly 2 trillion API requests per month?\u00a0 We\u2019re looking for a Lead API Engineer to help us design, build, and maintain the platform and codebase that powers AccuWeather\u2019s global weather API\u2019s, with the goal of delivering near real-time weather data and alerts to save lives, protect property, and help people prosper.\u00a0 Someone who strives for simplicity and performance yet exhibits a passion for innovation.\n\nWho You Are\nIn this role, you will create world class weather API\u2019s to be used by web and mobile applications, global handset manufacturers, large and small enterprises, and consumers alike.\u00a0 This technical leadership position will work cross-functionally with AccuWeather\u2019s Product Managers, key business stakeholders, and other Engineering teams, in an Agile-based environment, to rapidly deliver high-quality API\u2019s.\u00a0 If you are interested in one of the largest, most widely used API\u2019s in the world, and you enjoy technical challenges, apply today!\nThis position is available at our offices in State College, Pennsylvania, and New York City.\n\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES\n\n\nDesign, implement, and support AccuWeather\u2019s API frameworks and global API platforms\n\nDeep understanding of cloud infrastructures, Content Distribution Networks (CDNs), caching technologies, and scalability\n\nExpert understanding of Microsoft .NET, .NET Core, Web API, and C# technologies\n\nDesigns and writes code for complex features and functionality for high-performing software\n\nExperience in engineering and managing large enterprise / commercial API\u2019s to be consumed by both internal and external clients\n\nExperience with databases such as SQL Server, Oracle, Mongo DB, Azure Cosmos DB, Redis\n\nProvides technical leadership to and mentors fellow team members\n\nDemonstrates ability to present technical API solutions to internal and external cross-functional teams, leadership, and at conferences\n\nCollaborates with Product and other business units on timelines and roadmaps\n\nExhibits effective organizational and technical leadership skills\n\nEnsure deliverables are met with high quality, including those on tight timelines\n\n\n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\n\n\nBS/BA in related discipline with 8+ years\u2019 experience in related field - OR - MS/MA and 5+ years\u2019 experience in related field\n\nDemonstrated experience designing, developing, and supporting API solutions for consumption by high traffic, global, applications\n\nDemonstrated experience in software engineering and multiple object-oriented programming languages such as C#, Java, C++, Swift, etc.\n\nDemonstrated experience with CDN\u2019s, edge technologies, and caching\n\nDisplays a high level of critical thinking and analysis in bringing successful resolution to high-impact, complex, and inter-departmental challenges\n\nExperience in a CI / CD environment with tools such as Jenkins, SonarQube, GitHub, and others\n\nExperience presenting technical capabilities at conferences and/or prior teaching experience\n\nSelf-driven; strong problem-solving skills; adaptable, proactive, and willing to take ownership\n\nStrong communication skills; excellent collaboration, reporting, and analytical skills\n\n\n\n\n\n\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer. We provide equal opportunity to all qualified individuals regardless of race, color, religion, age, genetic information, gender, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, national origin, veteran orientation, or veteran status, pregnancy, disability, marital status or any other legally protected categories under local, state of federal laws.\u00a0 We believe a culture of diversity and inclusion provides unique perspectives that help make the workplace more innovative, engaging and profitable.", "job_location": "State College, PA or New York, NY", "job_title": "Lead Software Engineer, API", "job_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/jobs/1901439", "seen_time_epoch": 1577549228, "short_description": null, "tags_string": null}
{"found_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/", "full_description": "COMPANY\n\nAccuWeather, recognized and documented as the most accurate source of weather forecasts and warnings in the world, has saved tens of thousands of lives, prevented hundreds of thousands of injuries and tens of billions of dollars in property damage. With global headquarters in State College, PA and other offices around the world, AccuWeather serves more than 1.5 billion people daily to help them plan their lives and get more out of their day through innovative digital media properties, such as AccuWeather.com and mobile, as well as Business Solutions (AES), radio, television, newspapers, and the 24/7 AccuWeather Network.\n\nAdditionally, AccuWeather produces and distributes news, weather content, and video for more than 180,000 third-party websites. Among AccuWeather\u2019s many innovative and award-winning features free to the public are MinuteCast\u00ae Minute by Minute\u2122 forecasts with Superior Accuracy\u2122.\u00a0 Further, AccuWeather serves more than half of Fortune 500 companies and thousands of businesses globally.\n\n\n\nSUMMARY\n\nAccuWeather is looking for a\nDigital Journalist\nto join our team!\u00a0 This position will work out of our Headquarters office in State College, PA. We are looking for someone who is a creative thinker and constantly thinking outside the box. Our Digital Journalists also immerse themselves in the generation of unique, compelling story and video ideas. They research news stories and interview internal and external experts and excel at writing news stories under pressure of deadlines in a fast-paced environment.\n\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES\n\n\n\nParticipate in generation of unique, compelling weather-related story ideas.\n\nFollow trending topics on social networking, including Google, Twitter and Facebook for story ideas and headlines that optimize AccuWeather.com\u2019s reach in search engine optimization.\n\nWrite accurate stories that are well researched and attributed to necessary sources and update as necessary.\n\nInterview proper sources to enhance story content.\n\nRespond quickly to breaking news and weather situations, contributing to the news team's coverage of the event.\n\nCreatively use social media to send out breaking/interesting weather information and links to AccuWeather.com news stories.\n\nEditing and packaging of forecast and feature stories.\n\n\n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\n\n\n\nBachelor's degree in Journalism or a related communications field required.\n\n2-3 years of work experience required.\n\nDemonstrated journalism/media/social media experience.\n\nMust have strong writing skills and excellent knowledge of AP style.\n\nMust have knowledge and experience using Facebook, Twitter (experience using HootSuite preferred) and emerging social media platforms.\n\nMust be able to develop an understanding of basic scientific and meteorological concepts.\n\nMust be self-motivated, team-oriented and work well under pressure.\n\nMust have excellent communication skills and be proactive in seeking out interviews to enhance story content.\n\nBasic digital video editing skills are preferred.\n\nGood visual eye and basic photo editing skills.\n\n\n\nSKILLS\n\n\n\nSense of urgency\n. You act with the realization that efficiency is vital to success.\n\nA team player\n. You have the ability to consistently build and maintain strong working relationships with your direct teammates as well as co-workers throughout AccuWeather.\n\nCommunication\n. You have the ability to exchange information, both verbal and non-verbal, to anyone. You have solid speaking and writing skills.\u00a0 Your communication style ensures that all the organizational goals are achieved.\n\nPassion\n. You have a strong excitement and love for journalism. You pride yourself on being efficient at your job.\n\n\n\n\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer. We provide equal opportunity to all qualified individuals regardless of race, color, religion, age, genetic information, gender, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, national origin, veteran orientation, or veteran status, pregnancy, disability, marital status or any other legally protected categories under local, state of federal laws.\u00a0 We believe a culture of diversity and inclusion provides unique perspectives that help make the workplace more innovative, engaging and profitable.", "job_location": "State College, PA", "job_title": "Digital Journalist", "job_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/jobs/1818272", "seen_time_epoch": 1577549228, "short_description": null, "tags_string": null}
