{"found_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/", "full_description": "C\nOMPANY\n\n\nAccuWeather, recognized and documented as the most accurate source of weather forecasts and warnings in the world, has saved tens of thousands of lives, prevented hundreds of thousands of injuries and tens of billions of dollars in property damage. With global headquarters in State College, PA and other offices around the world, AccuWeather serves more than 1.5 billion people daily to help them plan their lives and get more out of their day through innovative digital media properties, such as AccuWeather.com and mobile, as well as Business Solutions (AES), radio, television, newspapers, and the 24/7 AccuWeather Network.\n\nAdditionally, AccuWeather produces and distributes news, weather content, and video for more than 180,000 third-party websites. Among AccuWeather\u2019s many innovative and award-winning features free to the public are MinuteCast\u00ae Minute by Minute\u2122 forecasts with Superior Accuracy\u2122.\u00a0 Further, AccuWeather serves more than half of Fortune 500 companies and thousands of businesses globally.\n\nSUMMARY\n\nThe Director of Infrastructure and Cloud Operations (ICO) positions, plans, directs, and manages the secure delivery of technology infrastructure on-premises and in the cloud, with a focus on a Cloud First strategy. This role is responsible for direction and oversight of technology teams that plan and execute on architecture, administration, and support of critical services and infrastructure in the cloud and on-premises including: networking, servers, storage, virtualization, containers, and standardized integration between cloud and on-premises resources. The successful candidate will have a strong technical background, demonstrated effectiveness in management and leadership, excellent written and verbal communication skills, and exceptional interpersonal skills.\n\n\n\nESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\n:\n\n\nEnsure the resilience, security, and reliability of operational technology systems in the cloud and on-premises.\n\nEnsure consistency of architecture, specifications, and nomenclature between cloud and on-premises resources.\n\nProvide a secure, consistent, and stable technology environment for production services, corporate infrastructure, and development needs.\n\nEnsure the architecture and related configuration enables and optimizes options for detailed cost accounting and reporting, particularly for cloud services, thereby providing clear and direct accountability for incurred cost of services.\n\nProvide leadership and management for multi-disciplinary teams of technology professionals.\n\nEnsure compliance with identity management and security practices set forth by the business.\n\n\n\nDevelop, implement, and/or maintain procedures and automated processes to monitor and respond to outages, service degradation, or other events that may negatively affect the operational status of production, development, and corporate infrastructure.\n\nRoutinely test and assess the technology operating environment, identifying and remediating any items that introduce unacceptable risk.\n\nPrepare regular technical and executive reports on operational status, planned and/or ongoing initiatives, and strategy for meeting future needs.\n\nReview, refresh, and develop technology policies as required.\n\n\n\nIdentify and implement system and process improvements that will enhance the usability, stability, and/or security of technology infrastructure.\n\nCollaborate with supply chain and vendors to establish/maintain robust and cost-effective equipment and services.\n\n\n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\n:\n\n\nA Bachelor\u2019s degree in Information Science, Computer Science, or a related field, or an equivalent combination of education and experience. An advanced degree is preferred.\n\n7+ years of personnel management in a technology environment.\n\n10+ years of technical management/administration of operational technology systems.\n\nHands-on technical expertise with implementation and administration of one or more cloud platforms is required. Azure is strongly preferred.\n\nStrong technical expertise in two or more specialty areas such as system administration, network administration, enterprise architecture, virtualization, information security, or cloud architecture.\n\nDemonstrated understanding of how to proactively identify and address operational technology needs.\n\nDemonstrated understanding of how to proactively identify and address information security risks.\n\nGeneral knowledge of identity management and information security best practices is required.\n\nFormal management/leadership training is strongly preferred.\n\nOne or more technical certifications, particularly in cloud computing, are strongly preferred.\n\nSecurity certifications such as CISSP or CISM are appealing.\n\n\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer. We provide equal opportunity to all qualified individuals regardless of race, color, religion, age, genetic information, gender, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, national origin, veteran orientation, or veteran status, pregnancy, disability, marital status or any other legally protected categories under local, state of federal laws.\u00a0 We believe a culture of diversity and inclusion provides unique perspectives that help make the workplace more innovative, engaging and profitable.", "job_location": "State College, PA", "job_title": "Director, Infrastructure and Cloud Operations", "job_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/jobs/2010160", "seen_time_epoch": 1577549228, "short_description": null, "tags_string": null}
{"found_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/", "full_description": "COMPANY\n\nAccuWeather, recognized and documented as the most accurate source of weather forecasts and warnings in the world, has saved tens of thousands of lives, prevented hundreds of thousands of injuries and tens of billions of dollars in property damage. With global headquarters in State College, PA and other offices around the world, AccuWeather serves more than 1.5 billion people daily to help them plan their lives and get more out of their day through innovative digital media properties, such as AccuWeather.com and mobile, as well as Business Solutions (AES), radio, television, newspapers, and the 24/7 AccuWeather Network.\n\nAdditionally, AccuWeather produces and distributes news, weather content, and video for more than 180,000 third-party websites. Among AccuWeather\u2019s many innovative and award-winning features free to the public are MinuteCast\u00ae Minute by Minute\u2122 forecasts with Superior Accuracy\u2122.\u00a0 Further, AccuWeather serves more than half of Fortune 500 companies and thousands of businesses globally.\n\n\n\nSUMMARY\n\nThe Video Engineer is a member of the engineering team that is responsible in maintaining the operation of a 24/7, multi-studio facility. These responsibilities include the maintenance and repair of all studio equipment and training of studio personnel for proper operation of equipment and systems. They will also participate in installation and/or modification projects for new or existing system.\n\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES:\n\n\nMaintains operational status of facility along with assuring proper performance of systems\n\nAssures that all studio systems and device conforms to Federal Communications Commission requirements in regard to operating and technical performances.\n\n\n\nAdvises, assists, and instructs operations personnel in matters pertaining to video and audio systems.\n\nTrains operations personnel in equipment use and operational procedures and evaluates performance of personnel compliance to engineering procedures.\n\nPerforms preventive maintenance, repairs, installation, and modification of video and audio systems.\n\nUpdates maintenance and repair documentation on all studio equipment.\n\nDemonstrates continuous effort to improve operations, workflow processes, and works cooperatively and jointly to provide quality seamless customer service.\n\nKeeps abreast of new developments in video production techniques, equipment, and industry standards.\n\nWorks independently and also cooperatively with other staff members, management, and outside support technicians.\n\nWill be scheduled for on-call status supporting operations personnel in evaluating and troubleshooting studio equipment failures or operational errors.\n\nWill provide engineering support during studio production events as required.\n\nWill provide operational support as a video tech when scheduled.\n\nWill provide technical maintenance and repair of Radio Broadcasting systems.\n\nWorks safely without presenting a direct threat to self or others.\n\nOther duties as assigned by the Chief Engineer.\n\n\n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\n\n\nA Bachelor\u2019s degree in a related field and at least 1 year of broadcast engineering experience or equivalent combination of education and experience.\u00a0 FCC or industry type certification would be a plus.\n\nAbility to troubleshoot system problems down to the equipment level.\n\nExperience with chroma keying and lighting for chroma key environments.\n\nExperience in working on installation projects.\n\nProficient in cable fabrication using appropriate crimping and soldering tools and techniques.\n\nExperience in reading system documentation and drawings.\n\nExperience in using video and audio test measurement equipment.\n\nKnowledge of industry video and audio standards and associated file formats.\n\nKnowledge of video productions techniques for both studio and remote environments\n\nAbility to communicate with colleagues, other department employees, with vendors and clients\n\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer. We provide equal opportunity to all qualified individuals regardless of race, color, religion, age, genetic information, gender, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, national origin, veteran orientation, or veteran status, pregnancy, disability, marital status or any other legally protected categories under local, state of federal laws.\u00a0 We believe a culture of diversity and inclusion provides unique perspectives that help make the workplace more innovative, engaging and profitable.", "job_location": "State College, PA", "job_title": "Video Engineer", "job_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/jobs/1707518", "seen_time_epoch": 1577549228, "short_description": null, "tags_string": null}
