elopment and marketing automation programs\n\nDistribute marketing communications and sales content as needed through marketing automation tools.\n\nManage executive biography communications across online, printed, and leadership event communications with tailored, documented updates, auditing online presence to ensure accuracy and consistency.\n\nManage publicity for leadership to include thought-leadership press placements with Public Relations team, media interview and event briefings, and execution.\n\nManage executive speaking pitches and placements to include targeted speaking event identification, proposal development, timeline, and vendor management.\n\nManage speaking events to include speech development and communications, planning, and execution logistics for both external and internal speeches.\n\nManage written staff communications under names of leadership as needed.\n\nResearch key contacts and manage communications sent under names of leadership to targeted decision-makers as defined.\n\nManage custom list and requested communications distribution to contact list\n\nSupport relevant marketing relations, events, and communications associated with leadership and AccuWeather.\n\nManage key messaging, master talk points, and presentation to consistently promote AccuWeather leadership and AccuWeather.\n\nOther corporate and executive communication duties as assigned.\n\n\n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS:\n\n\nMinimum of 5 years demonstrated experience in marketing communications and media & public relations experience required.\n\nExperience with Marketo (or similar programs like HubSpot, ExactTarget) and WordPress preferred\n\nBachelor's degree in Journalism, Public Relations, Communications or related field.\n\nExemplary written and verbal communication skills - Copywriting, speechwriting, and editing experience required.\n\nMust be able to communicate and present clearly and confidently at an executive level.\n\nAble to prioritize, multi-task, and work well under tight deadlines.\n\nCollaborative and team-oriented.\n\nDemonstrate high degree of confidentiality and professionalism at all times.\n\n\n\n\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer. We provide equal opportunity to all qualified individuals regardless of race, color, religion, age, genetic information, gender, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, national origin, veteran orientation, or veteran status, pregnancy, disability, marital status or any other legally protected categories under local, state of federal laws.\u202f We believe a culture of diversity and inclusion provides unique perspectives that help make the workplace more innovative, engaging and profitable.", "job_location": "State College, PA", "job_title": "Marketing Communications Manager", "job_url": "https://boards.greenhouse.io/accuweather/jobs/1952822", "seen_time_epoch": 1577549228, "short_description": null, "tags_string": null}
